.TH "lcd_device_register" 9 "lcd_device_register" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
lcd_device_register \- register a new object of lcd_device class.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct lcd_device *" lcd_device_register
.BI "(const char *name "  ","
.BI "struct device *parent "  ","
.BI "void *devdata "  ","
.BI "struct lcd_ops *ops "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "name" 12
the name of the new object(must be the same as the name of the
respective framebuffer device).
.IP "parent" 12
pointer to the parent's struct device .
.IP "devdata" 12
an optional pointer to be stored in the device. The
methods may retrieve it by using lcd_get_data(ld).
.IP "ops" 12
the lcd operations structure.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Creates and registers a new lcd device. Returns either an \fBERR_PTR\fP
or a pointer to the newly allocated device.
